      "id": "mcq_el2_ch10_001",
      "question": "Conduction velocity is calculated by dividing distance by:",
      "options": [
        "Proximal latency",
        "Distal latency",
        "Difference between proximal and distal latencies",
        "Total amplitude"
      ],
      "answer": "Difference between proximal and distal latencies",
      "explanation": "NCV is calculated as Conduction Distance divided by the conduction time difference (proximal latency minus distal latency)."
